How to connect local machine to remote machine:
first iniciate the github in the local repo
git init
first clone the remote repo with below command
git remote add origin github url
if you have any content to change then change and make it to the stage
git add . 
git commit - m " discription"
Create new branch 
git branch -m <branch name>
-------
Now you can push to the remote repo
git push -u origin main<branch name>
---------
If you face any kind of authentication issue or challenge (Permission, unable to access)
Use below command
To connect remote repo from local repo we need to configure authentication

git remote set-url origin https://username:password@github.com/arunponugoti1/Github_actions.git
Create access tocken and replace with password and add user name
---------------------------------------------------------------------
